    "patch_code": "private boolean isSafeReplacement(Node node, Node replacement) {\n  // No checks are needed for simple names.\n  if (node.isName()) {\n    return true;\n  }\n  Preconditions.checkArgument(node.isGetProp());\n\n  List<Node> children = node.children();\n  int numChildren = children.size();\n  if (numChildren == 0) {\n    throw new IllegalStateException(\"Expected at least one child\");\n  } else if (numChildren > 1) {\n    // Note: It could be more complicated than this.  See comments in the spec for `.`.\n    // Here we just consider flat object literals for safety checks.\n    return false;\n  }\n  \n  Node firstChild = children.get(0);\n  if (!firstChild.isName() || !isNameAssignedTo(firstChild.getString(), replacement)) {\n    return false;\n  }\n  return true;\n}",
